In Lean, for `Submodule`, the supremum is indeed computed pointwise, so `(sSup S) x = ⨆ s ∈ S, s x`.

Therefore, we can safely use `h₂ : (sSup D) x = ⨆ p ∈ D, p x`.

But in Lean, `D : DirectSumDecomposition M`, and `sSup D : Submodule`, so `(sSup D) x = ⨆ p ∈ (D : Set (Submodule)), p x`.

